Common Oracle Performance Dashboards

Using Oracle AWR views and cx_Oracle library for read data from database

paragraphs.text:
%pyspark
v_user=z.input("User name", "User_name")
v_pwd=z.input("User pwd", "Pwd")
v_conn=z.input("Connection", "host:port/sid")
import cx_Oracle

# Init connection OracleDBconnection 
def init_db(usr,pwd,conn):
    db = cx_Oracle.connect(usr,pwd,conn)
    return db

# Execute Oracle SQl with param and create SparkTable
def exec_Oracle_SQL(conn, sql, params, spark_table_name):
    cur=conn.cursor()
    if params == None:
        res=cur.execute(sql)
    else:
        res=cur.execute(sql, params)
    res_list = res.fetchall()
    if len(res_list) == 0:
        return spark_table_name+". Empty dataset. SparkTable coudn't be created"
    sqlContext.registerDataFrameAsTable(sqlContext.createDataFrame(res_list, [x[0] for x in res.description] ),spark_table_name)
    return spark_table_name+'. Register spark table succsessful'

db_con = init_db(v_user, v_pwd, v_conn)
res=exec_Oracle_SQL(db_con, "select * from dual", None, "dual")
if res == 1:
    print("Connection established")
cur = db_con.cursor()
cur.execute("select distinct dbid, dbid||' v.'||VERSION||' dbname='||DB_NAME||', host_name='||HOST_NAME||', platform='||PLATFORM_NAME||', start_time='||to_char(STARTUP_TIME, 'dd.mm.yyyy hh24:mi') description,STARTUP_TIME from dba_hist_database_instance order by 3 desc")
dbid_list = cur.fetchall()

%pyspark
v_dbid= z.select ("DB for analytics in AWR repository:", [(x[0],x[1]) for x in dbid_list])
named_params ={'dbid':v_dbid}
cur.execute("select snap_id snap_id, to_char(end_interval_time, 'dd.mm.yyyy hh24:mi') as end_interval_time from dba_hist_snapshot where dbid=:dbid order by 1",named_params)
a=cur.fetchall()

%pyspark
snap_beg= z.select ("Time begin(snap_beg):", a)
snap_end= z.select ("Time end(snap_end):", a)
inst = z.input("Instance number(inst) (* for all)","*")

%pyspark
DB_TIME_sql = "\
with \
    snap_time as (select to_char(max(end_interval_time),'dd.mm.yyyy hh24:mi:ss') t, snap_id \
                    from DBA_HIST_snapshot \
                    where dbid=:dbid and decode(:inst,'*',instance_number, :inst) = instance_number and \
                            snap_id between :snap_beg and :snap_end \
                    group by snap_id), \
    wait_time as    (select snap_id,  \
                        'Wait' as time_class ,  \
                        sum(time_waited_delta)/1000000 as value  \
                        from (select time_waited_micro - first_value(time_waited_micro) over (partition by dbid, instance_number, event_id order by snap_id ROWS 1 PRECEDING)  as time_waited_delta, \
                                        DBA_HIST_SYSTEM_EVENT.* \
                                    from DBA_HIST_SYSTEM_EVENT  \
                                    where   dbid=:dbid and  \
                                            decode(:inst,'*',instance_number, :inst) =instance_number  and \
	                                        snap_id in (select snap_id from  snap_time)  \
                                            and  wait_class <>'Idle')  \
                        group by snap_id \
                    ), \
    db_time as      (select snap_id, 'DBTime' as time_class, sum(value)/1000000 as value from \
                        (select snap_id,value - first_value(value) over(partition by dbid, instance_number, stat_id order by snap_id ROWS 1 PRECEDING) as value from dba_hist_sys_time_model \
                            where   dbid=:dbid and  \
                                    decode(:inst,'*',instance_number, :inst) =instance_number  and \
	                                snap_id in (select snap_id from  snap_time) \
                                    and stat_name ='DB time')  \
                        group by snap_id  \
                    ),  \
    cpu_time as     (select snap_id, 'CPU' as time_class, sum(value)/1000000 as value from   \
                        (select snap_id, value - first_value(value) over(partition by dbid, instance_number, stat_id order by snap_id ROWS 1 PRECEDING) as value from dba_hist_sys_time_model \
                            where   dbid=:dbid and  \
                                    decode(:inst,'*',instance_number, :inst) =instance_number  and \
	                                snap_id in (select snap_id from  snap_time) \
                                    and stat_name ='DB CPU') \
                        group by snap_id \
                    )   \
select * from ( select snap_time.t, wait_time.snap_id,wait_time.time_class, wait_time.value  from snap_time, wait_time where snap_time.snap_id = wait_time.snap_id \
union all \
select snap_time.t, db_time.snap_id,db_time.time_class, db_time.value  from snap_time, db_time where snap_time.snap_id = db_time.snap_id  \
union all  \
select snap_time.t, cpu_time.snap_id,cpu_time.time_class, cpu_time.value  from snap_time, cpu_time where snap_time.snap_id = cpu_time.snap_id  \
        )  \
order by snap_id  "

named_params ={'dbid':v_dbid, 'inst':inst, 'snap_beg':snap_beg, 'snap_end':snap_end}
exec_Oracle_SQL(db_con, DB_TIME_sql, named_params, "db_time_analytics")

WAIT_TIME_sql = "\
select stat.wait_class, stat.value,  snap_time.t, stat.snap_id \
 from (select to_char(max(end_interval_time),'dd.mm.yyyy hh24:mi:ss') t, snap_id \
from DBA_HIST_snapshot where dbid=:dbid and decode(:inst,'*',instance_number, :inst) =instance_number and snap_id between :snap_beg and :snap_end  \
group by snap_id) snap_time, \
(select snap_id,  \
       wait_class, round(sum(time_waited_delta)/1000000) as value  \
       from ( \
select time_waited_micro - first_value(time_waited_micro) over (partition by dbid, instance_number, event_id order by snap_id ROWS 1 PRECEDING)  as time_waited_delta, \
 DBA_HIST_SYSTEM_EVENT.* \
  from DBA_HIST_SYSTEM_EVENT  \
     where dbid=:dbid and  decode(:inst,'*',instance_number, :inst) =instance_number and \
     snap_id between :snap_beg and :snap_end and  wait_class <>'Idle' \
          ) \
   group by snap_id, wait_class   \
    order by snap_id, wait_class) stat \
     where stat.snap_id = snap_time.snap_id order by snap_time.t \
"

exec_Oracle_SQL(db_con, WAIT_TIME_sql, named_params, "wait_time_analytics")

cur = db_con.cursor()
cur.execute(WAIT_LIST_CLASS_SQL,named_params)

from DBA_HIST_snapshot where dbid=:dbid and decode(:inst,'*',instance_number, :inst) =instance_number and snap_id between :snap_beg and :snap_end  \
group by snap_id) snap_time, \
(select snap_id,  \
       wait_class, event_name, round(sum(time_waited_delta)/1000000) as value  \
       from ( \
select time_waited_micro - first_value(time_waited_micro) over (partition by dbid, instance_number, event_id order by snap_id ROWS 1 PRECEDING)  as time_waited_delta, \
 DBA_HIST_SYSTEM_EVENT.* \
  from DBA_HIST_SYSTEM_EVENT  \
     where dbid=:dbid and  decode(:inst,'*',instance_number, :inst) =instance_number and \
     snap_id between :snap_beg and :snap_end and  wait_class in ("+v_wait_class+") \
          ) \
   group by snap_id, wait_class, event_name   \
    order by snap_id, wait_class, event_name) stat \
     where stat.snap_id = snap_time.snap_id  and stat.value > 10 order by snap_time.t \
"

paragraphs.title: Metric and System Statistics
paragraphs.text:
%pyspark
db_params ={'dbid':v_dbid}
cur.execute("select metric_id, metric_name ||', unit: '||metric_unit as metric_name from DBA_HIST_METRIC_NAME where dbid =nvl(:dbid,(select dbid from v$database)) order by metric_name",db_params)
metric_array=cur.fetchall()
v_metric_id= z.select ("Metric name for next dashboards:", metric_array)

cur.execute("select stat_id, stat_name from DBA_HIST_STAT_NAME where dbid =:dbid order by stat_name",db_params)
sys_stat_array=cur.fetchall()
v_stat_id= z.select ("System statistics name for next dashboards:", sys_stat_array)


#Metric summary and history
metric_params ={'dbid':v_dbid, 'inst':inst, 'snap_beg':snap_beg, 'snap_end':snap_end, 'metric_id':v_metric_id}
METRIC_SUMMARY_SQL = "\
select to_char(end_time,'dd.mm.yyyy hh24:mi:ss') t, snap_id,  minval, maxval, average , METRIC_UNIT, metric_name \
from DBA_HIST_SYSMETRIC_SUMMARY where  dbid=:dbid and metric_id =:metric_id  and snap_id between :snap_beg and :snap_end and instance_number = decode(:inst,'*',instance_number, :inst) order by 2"
METRIC_HISTORY_SQL = "\
select to_char(end_time,'dd.mm.yyyy hh24:mi:ss') t, snap_id,  value, METRIC_UNIT, metric_name \
from DBA_HIST_SYSMETRIC_HISTORY where  dbid=:dbid and metric_id =:metric_id  and snap_id between :snap_beg and :snap_end and instance_number = decode(:inst,'*',instance_number, :inst) order by 2"

print(exec_Oracle_SQL(db_con, METRIC_SUMMARY_SQL, metric_params, "metric_summary_analytics"))
print(exec_Oracle_SQL(db_con, METRIC_HISTORY_SQL, metric_params, "metric_history_analytics"))

#Sys_stat
sysstat_params ={'dbid':v_dbid, 'inst':inst, 'snap_beg':snap_beg, 'snap_end':snap_end, 'stat_id':v_stat_id}
SYSSTAT_SQL =" select  \
                (select to_char(min(end_interval_time),'dd.mm.yyyy hh24:mi:ss') from dba_hist_snapshot a where a.snap_id = s.snap_id and a.dbid =s.dbid and a.instance_number = decode(:inst,'*',instance_number, :inst)) end_interval_time, 'Instance='||s.INSTANCE_NUMBER as INSTANCE_NUMBER,  \
                  (VALUE - first_value(VALUE) over (partition by s.dbid, s.instance_number, s.STAT_ID order by s.snap_id ROWS 1 PRECEDING)) as value, stat_name \
                    from DBA_HIST_SYSSTAT s \
                    where dbid=:dbid and snap_id between :snap_beg and :snap_end and instance_number = decode(:inst,'*',instance_number, :inst) and s.STAT_ID = :stat_id   \
                    order by end_interval_time "
print(exec_Oracle_SQL(db_con, SYSSTAT_SQL, sysstat_params, "sysstat_analytics"))

#sys_time_model
SYSTIME_MODEL_SQL="select  \
                (select to_char(min(end_interval_time),'dd.mm.yyyy hh24:mi:ss') from dba_hist_snapshot a where a.snap_id = s.snap_id and a.dbid =s.dbid and a.instance_number = decode(:inst,'*',instance_number, :inst)) end_interval_time, 'Instance='||s.INSTANCE_NUMBER as INSTANCE_NUMBER,  \
                  (VALUE - first_value(VALUE) over (partition by s.dbid, s.instance_number, s.STAT_ID order by s.snap_id ROWS 1 PRECEDING)) as value, stat_name \
                    from DBA_HIST_SYS_TIME_MODEL s \
                    where dbid=:dbid and snap_id between :snap_beg and :snap_end and instance_number = decode(:inst,'*',instance_number, :inst)   \
                    order by end_interval_time"
print(exec_Oracle_SQL(db_con, SYSTIME_MODEL_SQL, named_params, "systime_model_analytics"))

paragraphs.text:
%pyspark
SQL_rank_type = z.select("Choose TOP SQL Category", [("rank_time","Elapsed"),("rank_cpu","CPU"),("rank_io","User I/O"),("rank_cc","Concurrency"),("rank_cl","Cluster"),("rank_ap","Application"),("rank_java","Java"),("rank_pl","PLSQL")])
SQL_rank = z.input("Input tops threshold for choosen category","50")
sql_top_params = named_params.copy()
sql_top_params.update({"rank_type":SQL_rank_type, "rank":SQL_rank}) 
TOPSQL_SQL = "\
select * from \
(select * from  \
(select sql_id, dbid,  \
       executions, \
       elapsed_time, \
       CPU_TIME, \
       IOWAIT, \
       APWAIT, \
       CCWAIT, \
       PLSEXEC, \
       JAVEXEC, \
       CLWAIT,  \
       DENSE_RANK() OVER (order by elapsed_time DESC) rank_time, \
       DENSE_RANK() OVER (order by CPU_TIME DESC) rank_cpu, \
       DENSE_RANK() OVER (order by IOWAIT DESC) rank_io, \
       DENSE_RANK() OVER (order by CCWAIT DESC) rank_cc, \
       DENSE_RANK() OVER (order by APWAIT DESC) rank_ap, \
       DENSE_RANK() OVER (order by PLSEXEC DESC) rank_pl, \
       DENSE_RANK() OVER (order by CLWAIT DESC) rank_cl, \
       DENSE_RANK() OVER (order by JAVEXEC DESC) rank_java \
    from  \
(select sql_id, max(dbid) dbid, sum(executions_delta) executions, \
       round(sum(elapsed_time_delta)/1000000) elapsed_time, \
       round(sum(CPU_TIME_DELTA)/1000000) CPU_TIME, \
       round(sum(IOWAIT_DELTA)/1000000) IOWAIT, \
       round(sum(APWAIT_DELTA)/1000000) APWAIT, \
       round(sum(CCWAIT_DELTA)/1000000) CCWAIT, \
       round(sum(PLSEXEC_TIME_DELTA)/1000000) PLSEXEC, \
       round(sum(JAVEXEC_TIME_DELTA)/1000000) JAVEXEC, \
       round(sum(CLWAIT_DELTA)/1000000) CLWAIT \
       from dba_hist_sqlstat  where dbid=:dbid \
            and snap_id between :snap_beg and :snap_end \
            and instance_number = decode(:inst,'*',instance_number, :inst)  \
       group by sql_id) \
       ) \
        where  \
           decode(:rank_type,'rank_cpu',rank_cpu,'rank_io',rank_io,'rank_cc',rank_cc,'rank_cl',rank_cl, \
                        'rank_ap',rank_ap,'rank_java',rank_java,'rank_pl',rank_pl,'rank_time', rank_time ) < :rank    \
        ) \
 UNPIVOT ( v_time FOR wait_class IN (ELAPSED_TIME, \
       CPU_TIME, \
       IOWAIT, \
       APWAIT, \
       CCWAIT, \
       PLSEXEC, \
       JAVEXEC, \
       CLWAIT))    "
                        
print(exec_Oracle_SQL(db_con, TOPSQL_SQL, sql_top_params, "sqltop_analytics"))

paragraphs.text:
%pyspark
v_sql_id = z.input("Input sql_id for analysing","sql_id")
sql_id_params = named_params.copy()
sql_id_params.update({"sql_id":v_sql_id})
SQL_ID_SQL="\
select * from ( \
      select snap_id,(select to_char(s.end_interval_time,'dd.mm.yyyy hh24:mi:ss') from dba_hist_snapshot s  \
                        where s.snap_id =ss.snap_id and s.dbid = ss.dbid and s.instance_number=ss.instance_number) snap_time, \
              to_char(instance_number) as instance_number,            \
              sql_id, to_char(plan_hash_value) as plan_hash_value, \
              iowait_delta/decode(executions_delta,0,1,executions_delta) \"IO per exec\", \
              ccwait_delta/decode(executions_delta,0,1,executions_delta) \"Concurrency per exec\", \
              clwait_delta/decode(executions_delta,0,1,executions_delta) \"Cluster per exec\", \
              apwait_delta/decode(executions_delta,0,1,executions_delta) \"Application per exec\", \
              plsexec_time_delta/decode(executions_delta,0,1,executions_delta) \"PLSQL per exec\", \
              javexec_time_delta/decode(executions_delta,0,1,executions_delta) \"Java per exec\", \
              DISK_READS_DELTA/decode(executions_delta,0,1,executions_delta) \"Disk_read per exec\", \
              BUFFER_GETS_DELTA/decode(executions_delta,0,1,executions_delta) \"Buffer gets per exec\", \
              ROWS_PROCESSED_DELTA/decode(executions_delta,0,1,executions_delta) \"Row processed per exec\", \
              elapsed_time_delta/decode(executions_delta,0,1,executions_delta) \"Elapsed time per exec\", \
              cpu_time_delta/decode(executions_delta,0,1,executions_delta) \"Cpu time per exec\", \
              executions_delta as \"Executions\" \
        from dba_hist_sqlstat ss where \
            sql_id  =:sql_id and \
            dbid = :dbid and instance_number = decode(:inst,'*',instance_number, :inst) and \
            snap_id between :snap_beg and :snap_end) \
      unpivot \
      (v_time for stat_per_exec in ( \"IO per exec\",\"Concurrency per exec\", \"Cluster per exec\", \"Application per exec\", \"PLSQL per exec\", \"Java per exec\", \
                                     \"Disk_read per exec\", \"Buffer gets per exec\", \"Row processed per exec\", \"Elapsed time per exec\", \"Cpu time per exec\", \"Executions\"  )) "

print(exec_Oracle_SQL(db_con, SQL_ID_SQL, sql_id_params, "sql_stat_detail_analytics"))

SQL_ASH_SQL="\
with stat_full as ( \
    select dbid, snap_id, instance_number, \
        SQL_PLAN_HASH_VALUE, SQL_PLAN_LINE_ID||'-'|| \
            SQL_PLAN_OPERATION||' '|| \
            SQL_PLAN_OPTIONS as plan_line, \
            session_state, current_obj# , \
            decode(session_state,'ON CPU','CPU',event) event, SERVICE_HASH, \
            count(*) full_count, count(distinct sql_exec_id) exec_count \
    from dba_hist_active_sess_history  \
    where sql_id =:sql_id and \
            dbid = :dbid and \
            instance_number = decode(:inst,'*',instance_number, :inst) and \
            snap_id between :snap_beg and :snap_end \
    group by dbid, snap_id,instance_number, SQL_PLAN_HASH_VALUE, \
                SQL_PLAN_LINE_ID||'-'|| \
                SQL_PLAN_OPERATION||' '||  \
                SQL_PLAN_OPTIONS, session_state, current_obj#, \
                decode(session_state,'ON CPU','CPU',event), SERVICE_HASH) \
select to_char(stat_full.instance_number), to_char(stat_full.SQL_PLAN_HASH_VALUE), \
        stat_full.plan_line, stat_full.event, serv.service_name, \
        stat_full.session_state, to_char(stat_full.current_obj#) as current_obj_num, \
       stat_full.full_count, stat_full.exec_count \
from  stat_full, DBA_HIST_SERVICE_NAME serv \
  where  stat_full.dbid = serv.DBID \
    and stat_full.SERVICE_HASH  = serv.SERVICE_NAME_HASH "

print(exec_Oracle_SQL(db_con, SQL_ASH_SQL, sql_id_params, "sql_ash_analytics"))

%sql
select snap_id, snap_time, concat("Instance=",instance_number ) as inst_num, concat("Plan=",plan_hash_value) as plan, v_time as executions from sql_stat_detail_analytics where stat_per_exec in ('Executions') order by snap_id

paragraphs.title: SQL Details. Times per exec
paragraphs.text:
%sql
select * from sql_stat_detail_analytics where stat_per_exec in ('Cluster per exec','IO per exec','Concurrency per exec','Cluster per exec','Application per exec','PLSQL per exec','Java per exec','Elapsed time per exec','Cpu time per exec') order by snap_id

paragraphs.title: SQL Details. Reads per exec
paragraphs.text:
%sql
select * from sql_stat_detail_analytics where stat_per_exec not in ('Executions', 'Row processed per exec','Cluster per exec','IO per exec','Concurrency per exec','Cluster per exec','Application per exec','PLSQL per exec','Java per exec','Elapsed time per exec','Cpu time per exec') order by snap_id
